      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CYCLONE JENNI (8) resumes for new trainer Rickie Alchin after showing ability at her maiden campaign in Victoria, highlighted by a debut win at Melton. May need a bit of luck negotiating a very wide starting position but is likely to have developed with maturity. Readied with two city trials and is proven fresh so can kick off with a win. Stablemate KIKI MEISTER (9) drew on this row but worked forward and led before sticking on for a close fourth when resuming, beaten a neck at Goulburn. Has plenty of upside and is capable of playing a major role with even luck. LINE OF COURAGE (2) took a long time to win her maiden but achieved it in good style at this circuit and distance last week. Draws well so could be competitive again. BELIEVE IN CARMER (5) has had six weeks off since she finished runner-up from the back line at this circuit and distance last time but has been kept ticking over with two trials and has some upside.",
